    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Up for sale is a mechanically sound 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the iconic S54 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six engine and a 6-speed manual transmission. This driver-focused example boasts a linear power delivery and an 8,000 RPM redline, supported by a factory-spec limited-slip differential. Technical highlights include a recently completed VANOS system service and a reinforced rear subframe to ensure structural rigidity under high-torque loads. The suspension geometry remains tight, utilizing refreshed bushings for precise turn-in and communicative steering feel. While the exterior displays minor road-derived patina and the interior shows light bolster wear, the powertrain and chassis are dialed in for peak performance. A well-sorted enthusiast car that prioritizes analog engagement and mechanical longevity.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 38
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
      "description": "Used sedan. Good condition. Well-maintained mechanicals. Clean interior. Ready for immediate sale.",
